{{Infobox journal | title = Nature Geoscience | cover = [[File:Nature Geoscience cover.gif]] | editor = Heike Langenberg | discipline = [[Geosciences]] | abbreviation = Nat. Geosci. | publisher = [[Nature Publishing Group]] | country = | frequency = Monthly | history = 2008-present | impact = 13.941 | impact-year = 2016 | website = http://www.nature.com/ngeo/ | link2 = http://www.nature.com/ngeo/archive/ | link2-name = Online archive | OCLC =187319519 | LCCN = 2008203703 | CODEN =NGAEBU | ISSN =1752-0894 | eISSN =1752-0908 }} '''''Nature Geoscience''''' is a monthly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] published by the [[Nature Publishing Group]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Heike Langenberg. It was established in January 2008.
== Scope == The journal covers all aspects of the [[Earth sciences]], including [[theory|theoretical research]], [[Conceptual model|modelling]], and [[field work]]. Significant related work in other fields, such as [[atmospheric sciences]], [[geology]], [[geophysics]], [[climatology]], [[oceanography]], [[paleontology|palaeontology]], and [[space science]], is also published. <ref name=about> {{Cite web | title = About the journal | work = Nature Geoscience | publisher = [[Nature Publishing Group]] | url = http://www.nature.com/ngeo/about_journal.html | accessdate =2011-07-30}}</ref>
